{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse and an intent to make restitution by partially repaying the embezzled funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is disproportionately punitive for a $25,000 offense involving a first-time offender. Balancing the need for deterrence and punishment for the breach of fiduciary duty with the defendant's lack of prior record, a 6-month period of incarceration is appropriate.",
  "verdict": 6
}
